node.text:
Do you think privacy is possible in 2021? In this new privacy panel I share my 1st Hacking Stories, Open Source privacy tools, and elitism in Tech Culture. We talk about the state of US privacy laws, and World standards. The panel has many leading infosec experts talking together as we learn, debate, laugh and talk about some of today’s pressing security and privacy concerns.
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Happy new year! Llama loves you 🦙 - I've never told you the origin story behind my love for llamas. When I was 17, I had my very first panic attack and my pain condition came to the forefront of my life. I was NOT prepared for extreme pain and anxiety that gripped me 24/7. 😭

I spent the following years trying different medications and therapies to help with the mental and physical issues. When things got very intense, I would go for a walk and there was a llama farm right nearby my house. One of these super cute llamas (I called her Lola) always seemed to sense I was struggling. Lola always met with me and stood there for as long as I needed.. in sort of this unspoken mutual understanding. 🥰 I remember one day, I was having 9/10 pain and panic... I ran to Lola sobbing, she stayed with me for 2 hours until they forced her to go inside for the night. 

I'm still always learning in my pain and mental health journey, but I will never forget Lola and the connection I've felt with llamas and alpacas to this day. May this year be filled with better health, self awareness, kindness and understanding for all in 2021! 🤗 
.
.
.
.
